net.viktorc.pp4j.api

Interface ProcessExecutor

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    JavaProcessExecutorService, ProcessExecutorService
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    JavaProcessPoolExecutor, ProcessPoolExecutor, SimpleProcessExecutor

    public interface ProcessExecutor
    An interface that defines an executor that encapsulates a process and serves as a handle for having the process execute submissions.
    Author:
    Viktor Csomor

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean execute(Submission<?> submission)
      Sequentially writes the specified commands to the process and blocks until they are processed.

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        boolean execute(Submission<?> submission)
        Sequentially writes the specified commands to the process and blocks until they are processed. The result of the submission, if there is one, can be subsequently accessed by calling the Submission.getResult() method.
        Parameters:
        submission - The submission to execute.
        Returns:
        Whether the submission was executed. If the executor is not running, busy processing an other submission, or stopped before it could complete the execution of the submission, false is returned; otherwise the submission is processed and true is returned once it's successfully executed.
